FROM (VALUES
  ('e26fc097-16bd-53e5-b167-6897b1579645', 'HTT_RF06', 'IND_HTT_D02', 'HTT_RF06_DR03_SP01', 'Valet operates in Accommodation & Facilities Operations within Hospitality, Travel & Tourism, where the workplace setting involves guest arrival/movement, valet or front-office requests, room/service readiness, housekeeping/facility handoff, complaint resolution, and shift handover. It handles inputs and evidence such as guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record. Day to day, the role checks role-specific inputs, notices missing details or exceptions, updates trackers or review files, prepares handoff evidence, and escalates unresolved issues. The role handles routine checks, evidence preparation, and handoff within Accommodation & Facilities Operations; it escalates exceptions requiring senior judgement, formal approval, regulated sign-off, or authority beyond its role boundary. Output proof for this role includes guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record. Its role-environment RIASEC alignment is RIC (Realistic / Investigative / Conventional), reflecting practical, hands-on, field, tool, physical, operational, or technical execution work; analysis, diagnosis, investigation, testing, evidence interpretation, or problem solving; structured records, process control, compliance, documentation, scheduling, or accuracy-focused work.', 'R', 'I', 'C', 'RIC', 'Valet is mapped to RIC because its Accommodation / Guest Services / Facility Support Operations environment involves front-office, guest movement, parking/valet, room or service readiness, housekeeping/facility handoff, and hospitality service recovery. Realistic / Investigative / Conventional is relevant because the role uses practical, hands-on, field, tool, physical, operational, or technical execution work; analysis, diagnosis, investigation, testing, evidence interpretation, or problem solving; structured records, process control, compliance, documentation, scheduling, or accuracy-focused work while producing evidence such as guest-service checklist, valet/room/facility readiness log, service recovery note, shift handover, and guest feedback record.', 'Checks guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record against the current Accommodation & Facilities Operations requirement; notices missing fields, mismatched values, timing gaps, quality exceptions, or unresolved handoff items; updates the relevant tracker, checklist, issue note, review file, or handoff record; proves the behaviour through guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record.', 'Valet works in Accommodation & Facilities Operations within Hospitality, Travel & Tourism. The role context is guest arrival/movement, valet or front-office requests, room/service readiness, housekeeping/facility handoff, complaint resolution, and shift handover; its work is evidenced through guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record.', 'Valet: checks guest arrival/movement, valet or front-office requests, room/service readiness, housekeeping/facility handoff, complaint resolution, and shift handover; reviews role inputs and exceptions in Accommodation & Facilities Operations; updates the relevant tracker or checklist; prepares guest-service checklist; valet/room/facility readiness log; service recovery note; shift handover; guest feedback record; escalates items needing senior approval, regulated sign-off, or cross-team decision authority.', 'Valet output evidence includes: vehicle receipt and token log with guest name, vehicle identifier, time, and bay reference; parking bay movement register showing vehicle pick-up/drop-off sequence and handler initials; vehicle damage, missing-item, or key-handover exception note with supervisor escalation status; guest vehicle handover confirmation recorded at shift close.', '{"numerical_reasoning": 69.0, "logical_reasoning": 76.0, "verbal_reasoning": 60.0, "spatial_reasoning": 84.0, "data_interpretation": 70.0, "pattern_recognition": 73.0}'::jsonb, '{"openness": 3.0, "extraversion": 3.0, "agreeableness": 3.0, "conscientiousness": 5.0, "emotional_stability": 5.0}'::jsonb, '{"impact": 4.0, "status": 3.0, "autonomy": 2.0, "security": 4.0, "financial": 4.0, "lifestyle": 2.0, "creativity": 2.0, "leadership": 3.0}'::jsonb, '{"areas": ["Spatial Reasoning", "Logical Reasoning", "Pattern Recognition"], "rationale": "Valet depends most on spatial reasoning, logical reasoning, pattern recognition because the work involves field execution, technical checking, safety awareness, practical problem solving, and structured site follow-up. Lower readiness in the mandatory areas should trigger bridge practice rather than automatic rejection unless the role is safety, license, or authority gated."}'::jsonb, '{"traits": ["Conscientiousness", "Emotional Stability", "Agreeableness"], "rationale": "Valet benefits from conscientiousness, emotional stability, agreeableness because the role requires field execution, technical checking, safety awareness, practical problem solving, and structured site follow-up. These traits should adjust confidence and coaching focus, not act as a hard exclusion rule."}'::jsonb, '{"values": ["Financial Growth", "Impact", "Security"], "rationale": "Valet aligns best with learners who value financial growth, impact, security because the role environment involves field execution, technical checking, safety awareness, practical problem solving, and structured site follow-up. Work values should be used to prioritise role options, not to prove technical ability."}'::jsonb, 'Preferred', 'Hospitality; Tourism; BBA; Event Management; Any degree with customer-service or operations portfolio', true),
